  "text": "It is generally accepted that the transactivation of growth factor receptors participates in GPCR-mediated ERK1/2 phosphorylation [CITATION_1] . Breast cancer cells are known to transactivate ERK1/2 through FFA1, involving Src and EGFR [CITATION_2] . To assess the role of EGFR in the FFA1-induced ERK1/2 pathway in HEK293 cells, serum-starved FFA1-HEK293 cells were treated with AG1478 (EGF receptor inhibitor) and GM6001 (MMP inhibitor), followed by stimulation with LA.",
